user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters: in GLAM, archivists and librarians are desperate for people to do things with their data, but resource limits are a real problem, as are problems with their sometimes-rather-ropey 'shape' (cataloguing, metadata) and scales of data  #digitalhumanities #digihums
user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters, on responses from the GLAM sector, highlights a degree of scepticism around the notion of DH: 'I don't think it really needs very much'. Focus instead on 'digital scholarship' #digitalhumanities #digihums
user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters: 3Ô∏è‚É£ very few scholars rely on educational partners; 4Ô∏è‚É£ there is no 'DH 101' owing to the broad nature of the discipline. #digitalhumanities #digihums
user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters on findings with relation to skills in universities: 1Ô∏è‚É£ DH skills are introduced too late; 2Ô∏è‚É£ increased digital literacy and critical thinking need to be encouraged across the whole educational spectrum ... #digitalhumanities #digihums
user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters: 7 universities currently offer taught degree programs in DH (four of which have centre in DH); many others offer optional modules. There was an expectation among survey respondents that the number of hours of DH teaching would increase #digitalhumanities #digihums
user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters outlining the national picture that emerged: there are 13 centres in the UK dedicated specifically to DH. The @ahrcpress and @britac_news are, sadly, essentially the sole sources of funding in DH.  #digitalhumanities #digihums
user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters: 4Ô∏è‚É£ 'it's difficult to know where to publish your work in DGH'; 5Ô∏è‚É£ 'it's hard to get bids for funding for interdisciplinary work fairly assessed'. #digitalhumanities #digihums
user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters: Several common threads in all responses, though: 1Ô∏è‚É£ 'DH is all about networking'; 2Ô∏è‚É£ 'it's a challenge for ECRs, who feel that they have tp badge themselves somehow'; 3Ô∏è‚É£ 'some employers only really want traditional scholars' ... #digitalhumanities #digihums
user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters unpicks the divergence in views of DH among survey respondents, including suggestions that DH may 'just be about revenue generation', as well as others that DH specialists are involved heavily in teaching #digitalhumanities #digihums
user_description: Wannabe medievalist; PhD student @ExeterModLangs looking at Anglo-Norman didactic literature. Also Tweeting @ExeModLangsPGs & @ExeterUniChess.

text: .@jfwinters: Recognising the breadth of what DH covers is essential when we look to understand the support that needs to be offered #digitalhumanities #digihums

text: .@jfwinters: Most respondents worked in a research-intensive university, with 25% at lecturer / senior lecturer level. Variation was most evident, though, in research specialisms: 14 separate subjects were only mentioned by one person each! #digitalhumanities #digihums

text: .@jfwinters: The survey included 18 interviewees and 92 respondents to a HE-focused and targeted survey, bringing in people at all stages in their careers; all of them had DH at the core of their work #digitalhumanities #digihums
